Hashtagged successfully... #FOODTROTTERS_FOODWAVE_1
Well it was my first ever effort to try out a food video , so I may not be a pro but anyway it's fun posting! 
Talking about the Ingredients, I used only 400gms of the Salmon for now!(in video I shared the whole fillets of fish how it looks)
For Marination- 2 tbsp greek yogurt , 1tbsp of kashmiri red chilli powder, 1tbsp of fenugreek leaf (kasoori methi), 1 tbsp vegetable oil, 1 tbsp of ginger garlic paste,1tbsp of garam masala,1/2 tbsp lime juice 
Mixed them well and marinated for next 2 hours.
After Marination was done, preheat the oven at 400 degrees for additional 10 minutes.
Bake it for 10 minutes respectively flipping each side of the fish.
Yes please be careful , Salmon is too soft, while flipping it might break so handle carefully. Honestly, my first time experience with Salmon,  fair enough I broke few of them !! 😅🤪
Post 20 minutes , "Smokey Bongo Salmon is ready"! Plating be like  with some grated pepper jack cheese on the top of the salmon ,alongside grated lettuce, little Mayo and Pudina Chutney !
